League Gothic Condensed Regular (LeagueGothic-Condensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'League Gothic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Condensed' = NID 1 'League Gothic Condensed'.

Pass

League Gothic Condensed Italic Regular (LeagueGothic-CondensedItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LeagueGothic-CondensedItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

League Gothic SemiCondensed Regular (LeagueGothic-SemiCondensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LeagueGothic-SemiCondensed', Everything looks good.

Pass

League Gothic SemiCondensed Regular (LeagueGothic-SemiCondensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'League Gothic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed' = NID 1 'League Gothic SemiCondensed'.

Pass

League Gothic SemiCondensed Italic Regular (LeagueGothic-SemiCondensedItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'League Gothic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed Italic' = NID 1 'League Gothic SemiCondensed Italic'.

League Gothic Italic (LeagueGothic-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LeagueGothic-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

League Gothic SemiExpanded Regular (LeagueGothic-SemiExpanded.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'LeagueGothic-SemiExpanded', Everything looks good.

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender (2434) match or exceed the unitsPerEm value (2000).
